# Implementation Plan - Granola Web (Copycat)

This plan outlines the steps to build a web-based "Granola" clone—a beautiful, local-first meeting notepad that records audio and uses AI to enhance notes.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **API Keys**: To keep costs extremely low while maintaining quality:
> - **LLM**: We will use **Google Gemini API** (specifically `gemini-1.5-flash`). It is incredibly cheap (often free within tier limits) and very fast.
> - **Transcription**: We will use **Groq Cloud** to run `whisper-large-v3`. It is much faster and cheaper than standard OpenAI Whisper.
> - *Fallback*: We can still support OpenAI keys if preferred.

> [!NOTE]
> **Tech Stack**:
> - **Framework**: Next.js 14+ (App Router)
> - **Styling**: Vanilla CSS (CSS Modules & Variables) for a bespoke, premium "Granola" look.
> - **Storage**: IndexedDB (via `idb`) for local-first data storage.
> - **AI Integration**:
>   - **Google Generative AI SDK** (for Gemini).
>   - **Groq SDK** (for high-speed Whisper transcription).

## Proposed Changes

### Project Setup
- Initialize a new Next.js project at `/Users/canerden/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/granola-web`.
- Implement **Gemini** & **Groq** client setup.
- Clean up default styles and implement a custom Design System in `globals.css` focusing on:
    - **Typography**: Inter (sans-serif) or similar clean font.
    - **Colors**: Warm off-whites, sharp blacks, and "grainy" textures/gradients.

### Core Components ([NEW])
#### `components/Layout/Shell.js`
- Main application shell with a Sidebar (History) and Main Area (Editor).

#### `components/Editor/NoteEditor.js`
- A clean, distraction-free text area for typing notes.

#### `components/Recorder/AudioRecorder.js`
- Uses `MediaRecorder` API to capture audio.
- Visual feedback (red dot, timer).
- **Optimization**: Convert audio to format suitable for Groq (m4a/mp3/wav) client-side or server-side.

#### `lib/db.js`
- Utility to interact with IndexedDB.

### AI Integration
#### `lib/ai/client.js`
- **Gemini Client**: Setup for `gemini-1.5-flash`.
- **Groq Client**: Setup for `whisper-large-v3`.

#### `lib/ai/actions.js` (Server Actions)
- `transcribeAudio(formData)`: Uploads file to Groq for transcription.
- `enhanceNotes(transcript, rawNotes)`: Sends prompt to Gemini Flash to merge and format into "Granola-style" meeting notes.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1. **Recording Test**: Click Record, talk, Stop.
2. **Transcription Test**: Verify audio is sent to Groq and text is returned accurately.
3. **Enhancement Test**: Verify Gemini Flash returns structured notes based on the transcript.
4. **Cost Check**: Verify usage in dashboards (if available) to confirm low footprint.
